Chef has three water bottles. At any point, if at least two of them are empty, she will fill them up. But if at most one bottle is empty, she will wait, and not fill them up now.
You are given three integers - B1,B2,B3. If B1=1, it means the first bottle is full, If B1=0, it means the first bottle is empty. Similarly B2 denotes whether the second bottle is full or empty
and B3 denotes for the third bottle. Output "Water filling time", if Chef has to fill the bottles now. If not, output "Not now".

​






#include <stdio.h>

int main() {
	int B1,B2,B3;
	scanf("%d%d%d",&B1,&B2,&B3);
	if(B1+B2+B3<=0) {
	    printf("Water filling time");
	} else {
	    printf("Not now");
	}

}
